# Supabase Integration Best Practices

## Backend API Service Structure
The main backend service is located in [lib/data/services/database/backend_api.dart](mdc:lib/data/services/database/backend_api.dart)

## Common Supabase Integration Issues

### 1. Mock Type Compatibility
When testing Supabase services, ensure proper mock setup:
```dart
// ✅ Correct: Include all required types in mock generation
@GenerateMocks([
  SupabaseClient,
  SupabaseQueryBuilder,
  PostgrestFilterBuilder,
  PostgrestBuilder,
  SupabaseStorageClient,
  StorageFileApi,
  GoTrueClient,
  User,
  Bucket,
  FileObject,
])
```

### 2. FileObject Constructor Requirements
FileObject requires `updatedAt` parameter:
```dart
// ✅ Correct
FileObject(
  bucketId: 'avatars',
  name: 'profile.jpg',
  id: 'profile-id',
  owner: 'owner-id',
  metadata: {'size': 1024},
  updatedAt: DateTime.now().toIso8601String(), // Required!
)

// ❌ Avoid: Missing updatedAt
FileObject(
  bucketId: 'avatars',
  name: 'profile.jpg',
  id: 'profile-id',
  owner: 'owner-id',
  metadata: {'size': 1024},
  // Missing updatedAt will cause compilation errors
)
```

### 3. Query Builder Type Safety
Ensure proper type handling for PostgrestFilterBuilder:
```dart
// ✅ Correct: Use proper return types
when(mockQueryBuilder.select()).thenAnswer((_) async => data);
when(mockFilterBuilder.eq('id', '123')).thenAnswer((_) async => result);

// ❌ Avoid: Type mismatches
when(mockQueryBuilder.select()).thenReturn(mockFilterBuilder); // May cause type conflicts
```

## Storage Operations

### Profile Image Upload
```dart
Future<String> uploadProfileImage(String userId, Uint8List fileBytes, String fileExt) async {
  final String path = '$userId/profile.$fileExt';
  
  // Check bucket existence
  final List<Bucket> buckets = await client.storage.listBuckets();
  final bool bucketExists = buckets.any((bucket) => bucket.name == 'avatars');
  
  if (!bucketExists) {
    throw Exception("Der Storage-Bucket 'avatars' existiert nicht.");
  }
  
  // Upload with proper options
  await client.storage.from('avatars').uploadBinary(
    path,
    fileBytes,
    fileOptions: FileOptions(
      cacheControl: '3600',
      upsert: true,
    ),
  );
  
  return client.storage.from('avatars').getPublicUrl(path);
}
```

### Profile Image Retrieval
```dart
Future<String?> getProfileImageUrl(String userId) async {
  try {
    final List<FileObject> files = await client.storage.from('avatars')
        .list(path: userId);
    
    final List<FileObject> userFiles = files.where(
      (file) => file.name.startsWith('profile.')
    ).toList();
    
    if (userFiles.isNotEmpty) {
      final String filePath = '$userId/${userFiles.first.name}';
      return client.storage.from('avatars').getPublicUrl(filePath);
    }
    
    return null;
  } catch (e) {
    // Handle storage errors gracefully
    return null;
  }
}
```

## Database Operations

### Profile Management
```dart
Future<Profile> getUserProfileById(String id) async {
  final response = await client.from('profiles').select().eq('id', id);
  if ((response as List<dynamic>).isEmpty) {
    return Profile(id: id); // Return empty profile for UI
  }
  
  final Map<String, dynamic> profileData = response.first;
  return Profile.fromJson(profileData);
}

Future<void> updateUserProfile(Profile profile) async {
  final Map<String, dynamic> profileJson = profile.toJson();
  profileJson.remove('email'); // Remove fields not in database
  profileJson.remove('imageUrl');
  
  if (profileJson['id'] == null || profileJson['id'].isEmpty) {
    final String? userId = client.auth.currentUser?.id;
    if (userId != null) {
      profileJson['id'] = userId;
    } else {
      throw Exception('Benutzer-ID konnte nicht ermittelt werden');
    }
  }
  
  await client.from('profiles')
      .update(profileJson)
      .eq('id', profileJson['id']);
}
```

## Error Handling Patterns
```dart
try {
  // Supabase operation
  await client.from('table').select().eq('id', id);
} catch (e) {
  if (e.toString().contains('permission denied')) {
    throw Exception("Keine Berechtigung für diese Operation");
  } else if (e.toString().contains('network')) {
    throw Exception("Netzwerkfehler - bitte Verbindung prüfen");
  }
  rethrow;
}
```

## Testing Supabase Services
```dart
// Mock setup
when(mockSupabaseClient.from('profiles')).thenReturn(mockQueryBuilder);
when(mockQueryBuilder.select()).thenReturn(mockFilterBuilder);
when(mockFilterBuilder.eq('id', 'user123')).thenAnswer((_) async => [profileData]);

// Test execution
final result = await service.getUserProfileById('user123');
expect(result.id, 'user123');
```

## Common Supabase Tables
- `profiles`: User profile information
- `hikes`: Available hiking trails
- `purchased_hikes`: User-hike associations
- `hike_images`: Images for hikes
- `waypoints`: Points of interest on hikes
- `hikes_waypoints`: Hike-waypoint associations with order

## Environment Configuration
Ensure proper environment setup:
```bash
# .env file
SUPABASE_URL=your_supabase_url
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_anon_key
DEV_MODE=true  # For development features
```
